Creamy Herbed Spinach Dip
  --America's Test Kitchen

10 oz frozen chopped spinach
1/2 c sour cream
1/2 c mayo
2 tbsp thin sliced scallions, white parts only, from 3 medium scallions
1 tbsp chopped fresh dill leaves
1/2 c packed flat leaf parsley leaves
1 small clove garlic, minced or pressed through garlic press (~ 1 tsp)
1/4 tsp hot pepper sauce (Tabasco)
1/2 tsp salt
1/4 tsp ground black pepper
1/2 medium red bell pepper, diced fine (~1/4 c)

Thaw spinach in microwave for 3 min at 40% power, edges should be thawed but not warm; center should be soft enough to be broken apart into icy chunks. (Can be thawed at room temp for 1.5 hrs, then squeezed of excess liquid) In food processor, process spinach, sour cream, mayo, scallions, dill, parsley, garlic, hot pepper sauce, salt, and pepper until smooth and creamy, ~30 s. Transfer mixture to medium bowl and stir in bell pepper, serve. Can cover with plastic wrap and refrigerated for up to 2 days.
